    <abstract>
      <t>Distributed Multi-Agent Systems consist of Agents and MCP Servers operating across multiple administrative domains, each with its own Identity Providers (IdPs) and Authorization Servers (AS). This document discusses the challenges and solution approaches for sharing authorization information securely and flexibly across domains, including the use of dynamic identity, interoperable claims, and verifiable credentials.</t>
